Basics
-----------------
datatypes

int   (1,2,3)
float (2.0,3.7)
str   ('Hello')
bool  (True , False)

complex (2 + 5j)


the datatype is not explicitly declared, its dynamically inferred

arthematic operators
-----------
+ add
- sub
* mul
/ div

// quotient
% remainder
** raise to/power

logical operators
--------------
== equals
>= greater than or equal to
<= less than or equal to
!= not equals
> greater than
< less than



sequences
---------------------
collection of datatypes

list        []
tuple       ()
dict        {'key':'value'}
set         {}


indexing and slicing
----------------
to retrieve the elements in the sequence

once a tuple is declared it cant be changed (immutable)


retrieve values using keys in a dictionary
dict[key] = value

____________________________________________________

if-else, for loop and while loop

syntax
if-else
_______________

if boolexpr:
	statement1
	statement2
else:
	statements

_______________


if-elif-else

elif
else if
_____________

while loop:



while boolexpr:
	statement1
	statement2
statement3 #outside while


keywords - break,continue and pass

break - when control encounters the break statement, loop will be exited
continue - when control encounters the continue statement , loop will skip the iteration
pass - when control encounters the pass statement , it does nothing


for loop:

for var in iterable:
	statement 1
	statement 2
statement 3 #outside for



list comprehension:


[expr for var in iter if boolexpr]

for var in iter:
	if boolexp:
		expr


